## Tips before your mason visit in Srinagar

A little preparation helps your booking go smoothly and saves time on site:

- **Take clear photos** of cracks, loose tiles, or damaged plaster when booking via WhatsApp or the website.
- **Clear the work area** — move furniture, rugs, and items away from walls or floors being repaired.
- **Note recent leaks** if plaster or tiles failed after plumbing issues, so the mason can check underlying damage.
- **List all areas** in one booking if they are in the same visit — for example, bathroom grouting and a hallway tile fix.
- **Be home or have someone available** to show the problem areas and discuss finish expectations.

If the job requires materials — tiles, cement, grout, or adhesive — your partner can advise on quantities and whether you should source them locally or they will bring standard supplies. For larger renovation work, a site visit quote is often the best way to plan budget and timeline.

